Newer Buildings in Cambridge, MA

This map was created as a result of the September Maptime Boston meetup. Ken Johnson walked particpants through using R to create maps with R markdown files using this example. This map is the result of me following along and creating my own map and R markdown file.

Lighter blues indicate an older building, while darker purples mean the building on the parcel was constructed more recently. Click on a parcel to see the address and the year the building was constructed.

Below is the R code used to generate the map above.

knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo=TRUE,fig.width=8, fig.height=4.5, comment=NA, warning=FALSE, message=FALSE)
options(width=100)

#import libraries
library(rgdal)
library(leaflet)

#read in the assessor's data
ass2015 = read.csv('data/Assessing_Building_Information.csv', 
               stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
#subset year built field and link to map IDs
ass_new = subset(ass2015, Actual.Year.Built>=1980) 
ass_new = ass_new[!duplicated(ass_new$GIS.ID),]

#read in parcel data
parcels2015 = readOGR('data/ASSESSING_ParcelsFY2015.shp', 
        'ASSESSING_ParcelsFY2015', stringsAsFactors=FALSE)

#merge the parcel and assessor information
new_parcels = parcels2015[parcels2015$ML %in% ass_new$GIS.ID,]
new_parcels = merge(new_parcels, ass_new, by.x='ML', by.y='GIS.ID')

#transform the data into Web Mercator projection
new_osm = spTransform(new_parcels, CRS("+init=EPSG:4326"))

#set the basemap and add data to it
base_map = leaflet() %>% 
  addProviderTiles('CartoDB.DarkMatter') %>% 
  setView(-71.128184, 42.3769824, zoom = 14) 

base_map %>% 
  addPolygons(data=new_osm)

#create the color palette
palette = c('#edf8fb', '#bfd3e6', '#9ebcda', 
            '#8c96c6', '#8c6bb1', '#88419d', '#6e016b')

year_built = new_parcels@data$Actual.Year.Built
colors = palette[cut(year_built, c(seq(1980, 2010, 5), 2015), 
                     include.lowest=TRUE, labels=FALSE)]
labels = toString(year_built)

#add the data and color palette to the basemap
base_map %>% 
  addPolygons(data=new_osm, 
              color='black', fillColor=colors) # Colors

#create html pop-ups and add them to the basemap
popups = apply(new_parcels@data, 1, function(parcel) {
         paste0('<p>', parcel['Location'], '<br>',
         'Year: ', parcel['Actual.Year.Built'], '<br></p>')
         })

base_map %>% 
  addPolygons(data=new_osm, 
              color='black', fillColor=colors, # Colors
              popup=unname(popups),            # Popups
              options=c(pathOptions(), popupOptions(minWidth=100)))

#display the final map
base_map %>% 
  addPolygons(data=new_osm, 
              color='black', fillColor=colors, # Colors
              weight=1, dashArray=1,           # Line weight
              opacity=0.8, fillOpacity=0.9,    # Transparency
              popup=unname(popups),            # Popups
              options=c(pathOptions(), popupOptions(minWidth=100)))
